fullText:
There are several cable identification methods as follows.
(a) Electrical methods include —
(i) audio frequency signal generator;
(ii) current injection;
(iii) pulse injection;
(iv) interrupted earth; and
(v) use of fault location equipment.
(b) Non-electrical methods include —
(i) visual tracing from a proven isolation point;
(ii) rodding of wiring enclosures; and
(iii) cable plans.
A non-electrical method shall not be used as the sole means of identification.
